Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded, sliced into thin strips) and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and pepper to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @peri peri seasoning{1} to the chicken and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{100%ml}. Stir to combine and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir the @peas{120%g} and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} through the chicken and sauce.

Once the rice is cooked, stir it into the chicken and sauce until well combined.

Just before you're ready to serve, add the @butter{20%g} to the pan and stir until melted.

When ready, share the peri peri chicken and rice between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!